result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael George Olds was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Michael George Olds in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 9:51 am. Count 1 DRI - state has complied with victim notification and no restitution requested - plead to count 2 & 3 - w/hold and place on probation for 18 months - costs/surcharges count 2 I/S 9 months of jail count 3 I/S 9 months consecutive to count 2 - AODA, no consume/possess or entry, emp/education, 100 hrs community service approved by P&P, no contact with victims or any property owed by the victims. Burns if all debts are paid he could apply for early discharge of probation. Olds agrees that is agreement after court explains that they have no control over early discharge. Court DRI count 1 and defendant pleads NC to counts 2 & 3. Court goes thru plea questionnaire and finds defendant is entering plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently by entering his plea and waiving right to JT, factual basis, adjudges guility of counts 2 & 3. State/Burns make final argument follow joint recommendation. Olds withholds statement. Court sentences to the following: Count 2 - I/S 9 months jail w/hold sentence and place on probation for 18 months -- conditions AODA and follow thru, no possession/consumption of alcohol, no entry into any bars/taverns, emp/eductation, 100 hours of community service within the 1st 6 months of probation, no contact with victims or any property owned by victims  (W.M.) , costs/surcharges on both counts. Count 3 I/S 9 months jail - w/hold sentence and place on probation for 18 months - I/S 9 months jail with same conditions as count 2 with no additional community service, costs/surcharges - all paid thru probation. 9 days credit if revoked - advised of DNA expungement, appeal rights given.
